        <div class="row3">
            <h3 id="bottom">
                Liu, Cixin in his fiction <em>The three body problem</em> stated that the best way to store human heritage is to "carve the words on the stone". <mark>Can we also retain the human memories in the digital stone so that humans in the far future will still learn them?</mark>
            </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="row1">
            <h2>
                We Women Recognize Ourselves – Not the Internet
            </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="row4">
            <h4>
                Sarah Storey
            </h4>
            <br>
            <p>
                After being born without a functioning left hand, Sarah Storey faced a lot of bullying and prejudice growing up. She didn’t let that stop her, though. Instead, she went on to become Britain’s most decorated Paralympian, earning 27 medals, including 17 gold medals, in cycling and swimming. (CROTEAU, 2023)
            <br>
            <br>
                Throughout her career, she has become a symbol of perseverance and excellence in Paralympic sports, inspiring countless individuals with disabilities to pursue their dreams in athletics. Her accomplishments have earned her widespread recognition and respect in the world of sports, making her one of Britain's most revered Paralympians.
            </p>
            <p>
                <br>
                <a href="http://127.0.0.1:3000/d:/DKU/DKU@Duke/assignment3-main/women" style="float: right;">
                    Learn more...
                </a>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="row5">
            <img src="assets/images/storey.jpg" alt="Sarah Storey">
        </div>
        <div class="row5">
            <img src="assets/images/Li.jpg" alt="Feifei Li">
        </div>
        <div class="row4">
            <h4>
                Feifei Li
            </h4>
            <br>
            <p>
                Born in Beijing, China on Oct. 30, 1976, Fei-Fei Li is a prominent figure in the field of artificial intelligence (AI) and computer vision. She is known for significant contributions to machine learning, particularly in areas like image recognition and visual understanding.
            <br>
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>ImageNet and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs):</strong> One of Fei-Fei Li's most significant contributions is her leadership in the development of ImageNet, a large-scale dataset of labeled images. This dataset played a crucial role in advancing the field of computer vision. Under her guidance, the ImageNet project organized the ImageNet Large Scale Visual Recognition Challenge (ILSVRC), which led to significant advancements in the accuracy of image classification through the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs).
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Pioneering Research in Computer Vision:</strong> Fei-Fei Li's research has greatly expanded our understanding of computer vision. Her work has been instrumental in enabling machines to recognize objects, scenes, and patterns in visual data, with applications ranging from autonomous vehicles to medical imaging.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                <br>
                <a href="http://127.0.0.1:3000/d:/DKU/DKU@Duke/assignment3-main/women" style="float: right;">
                    Learn more...
                </a>
            </p>
        </div>
